result.execSummary:
The defendant Damarkus R Tate was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Child Enticement-(Sexual Contact or intercourse), a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.07(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Damarkus R Tate in court with attorney Jeff Allen Schwarz.  Defendant Damarkus R Tate in custody.  Kevin Shomin for Cynthia Davis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Clerk;ds

Sentencing proceeds.  State has complied with victim notification.  Statements by counsel and defendant.  COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms or body armor; he must provide a DNA sample; pay the mandatory DNA surcharge; cannot vote until his civil rights are restored; comply with the sex offender resgistry requirements for a period of 15 years and cannot work or volunteer with children under the age of 16 years.  

Count 1:  COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE - 36 months with 26 days credit -  INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT - 18 months  -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION - 18 months; pay mandatory costs, assessments and surcharges by the end of the sentence or a civil judgment is to be entered against the defendant and subject to other collection.  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  1) no violations of criminal law rising to the level of probable cause; 2) pay any monetary amounts ordered but not paid while in the institution; 3) seek and maintain employment; 4) no contact with DAS (DOB: 2-4-99).

Court finds defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis;
-  DOC to collect monetary sums/amounts at the rate of 25% of prison funds.

Appeal rights given.  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence and Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief and Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgment received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.
Justice Point report received and filed./ds
Received from defense counsel

Defendant waives constitutional rights, enters a plea of GUILTY to amended Count 1 and is examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum  received and filed. On motion of the State, Court orders Counts 2 & 3 DISMISSED and read-in for sentencing purposes. 

Parties advised the Court will listen to statements by counsel, victim, a friend or relative of the defendant and defendant.  Any other statements must be in writing and provided to the Court 72 hours in advance of sentencing.  Restitution will be addressed at that time.

Court orders defendant remanded into the custody of the sheriff pending sentencing.
